'''Carovigno''' ({{lang-it|Stazione di Carovigno}}) is a railway station near the [[Italy|Italian]] town of [[Carovigno]], in the [[Province of Brindisi]], [[Apulia]]. The station lies on the [[Adriatic Railway|Adriatic Railway (Ancona–Lecce)]] and was opened in 1865. The train services are operated by [[Trenitalia]].

==Train services==
The station is served by the following service(s):

*Regional services (''Treno regionale'') Bari - Monopoli - Brindisi - Lecce

